{"questionId":"25411","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><strong>This question asks you to explore properties of a family of curves of the type</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math> <strong>for various values of</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> <strong>and</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>, <strong>where</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℕ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>On the same set of axes, sketch the following curves for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>2</mn></math>,&nbsp;clearly indicating any points of intersection with the coordinate axes.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/3d859220a9c51c4d3fdfa9792d879b66370df868.png\"></p>\n<p>approximately symmetric about the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>including cusp/sharp point at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Final&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong>&nbsp;</em>can be awarded if intersections are in approximate correct place&nbsp;with respect to the axes shown. Award&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1A1A0</strong></em>&nbsp;if graphs ‘merge’ or&nbsp;‘cross’ or are discontinuous at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis but are otherwise correct. Award&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A0A0A0</strong></em>&nbsp;if only one correct branch of both curves are seen.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;If they sketch graphs on separate axes, award a maximum of 2 marks for&nbsp;the ‘best’ response seen. This is likely to be&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1A0A0</strong></em>.</p>","meta":{"questionId":"25411","referenceCode":"22M.3.AHL.TZ2.1a.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"y2=x3, x≥0","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}